#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:4
msgid "Pioneer DDJ-SB2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:6
msgid ""
"The Pioneer DDJ-SB2 is an all-in-one USB :term:`MIDI` controller with a "
"built in sound card. It has controls for 2 decks that can be toggled between"
" decks to play with 4 decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:8
msgid ""
"`Manufacturer’s product page <https://www.pioneerdj.com/product/dj-"
"controllers/ddj-sb2/>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:9
msgid ""
"`Manufacturer's User Manual "
"<https://support.alphatheta.com/articles/23017624264857?product=4416570350105>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:10
msgid ""
"`Forum thread <https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/pinoneer-ddj-sb2-midi-"
"mapping/15373/26>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:15
msgid "Audio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:17
msgid ""
"The sound card has 2 RCA jacks for the main output. There are two headphone "
"jacks, one small (1/8“) and one large (1/4”) connector (each jack plays the "
"same channels, they cannot be used for independent signals). There is a "
"1/4\" microphone input with an adjustable gain knob. The microphone input is"
" mixed directly with the main RCA outputs in hardware. It is not available "
"to the computer, so cannot record or broadcast with the microphone input on "
"the controller. You could use the controller with a separate USB :ref:`audio"
" interface <hardware-audio-interfaces>` that has a microphone input for that"
" purpose. The microphone preamplifier is very noisy, so it is recommended to"
" keep the microphone gain knob all the way down when not using a microphone,"
" otherwise there will be noise added to the main RCA outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:24
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:26
msgid ""
"Pioneer has a `driver "
"<https://support.alphatheta.com/articles/23017814733465?product=4416570350105>`__"
" for Windows versions 7 and newer. Select the ASIO sound :term:`API` in "
"Mixxx’s Sound Hardware Preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:29
msgid "Mac OS X & Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:31
msgid ""
"The DDJ-SB2 is a USB class compliant :term:`MIDI` and audio device, so it "
"works with Mac OS X and Linux without any special drivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:34
msgid "User Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:36
msgid ""
"There are some user configurable options for this mapping. To change the "
"options, open the ``.js`` file in your controller for your Pioneer DDJ-SB2 "
"with a text editor such as KWrite or GEdit on GNU/Linux, Notepad on Windows,"
" or TextEdit on Mac OS X."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:38
msgid ""
"**blinkingSync**: If true the sync button blinks with the beat, if false led"
" is lit when sync is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:39
msgid ""
"**invertVinylSlipButton**: If true, the vinyl button activates slip. Vinyl "
"mode is then activated by using shift. Allows toggling slip faster, but is "
"counterintuitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:40
msgid ""
"**jogwheelSensivity**: Sets the jogwheels sensitivity. 1 is default, 2 is "
"twice as sensitive, 0.5 is half as sensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:41
msgid ""
"**jogwheelShiftMultiplier**: Sets how much more sensitive the jogwheels get "
"when holding shift. Set to 1 to disable jogwheel sensitivity increase when "
"holding shift."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:42
msgid ""
"**speedRateToNormalTime**: Time per step (in ms) for pitch speed fade to "
"normal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:43
msgid ""
"**showVumeterMaster**: If true Level-Meter shows VU-Main left & right. If "
"false shows level of channel: 1/3 2/4 (depending active deck)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:44
msgid ""
"**cutVumeter**: Cut’s Level-Meter low and expand upper. Fore example, at 0.5"
" only signals greater 50% show on the meter, expanded to full range"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:45
msgid "**twinkleVumeterAutodjOn**: If true VU-Level twinkle if AutoDJ is ON."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:46
msgid ""
"**jumpPreviewEnabled**: If true, when releasing the browser knob, the "
"preview deck jumps forward to “position”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:47
msgid ""
"**jumpPreviewPosition**: The place in the track to jump to, on a scale from "
"0 (beginning of track) to 1 (end of track)."
msgstr ""

