#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:82
msgid "Volume, equalizers & filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:84
msgid ""
"Between the decks the usual faders, crossfader and EQ knobs can be found. A "
"filter knob is also available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:86
msgid ""
"Knobs are available for the main and headphones level. These control the "
"controller’s built in sound card; they do not control the software gains in "
"Mixxx, so moving them does not move the main and headphone gain knobs on "
"screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:89
msgid ""
"The filter fade button changes the crossfader from fading the volumes "
"between decks to using filters to fade between decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:91
msgid "The TRIM knob controls the deck’s gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:94
msgid "Jogwheels, tempo & vinyl mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:96
msgid ""
"When a deck is paused, the jogwheel allows you to browse through a track. If"
" you want to browse faster, hold shift while using the jogwheel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:98
msgid ""
"When a deck is playing, using the jogwheel allows you to temporarily change "
"the tempo of the playing track. Again, holding shift exaggerates this "
"effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:100
msgid ""
"The tempo slider allows changing the tempo of each deck. This normally "
"changes the pitch of a track, but you can make the pitch stay constant by "
"pressing the “key lock / tempo range” button. Additionally, with shift, the "
"“key lock / tempo range” will fade the tempo slowly to 0. The fading speed "
"can be customized with the speedRateToNormalTime mapping option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:103
msgid ""
"Vinyl mode makes the jogwheels emulate the way turntables work. Vinyl mode "
"can be toggled by pressing the “vinyl / slip” button. Touching the outer "
"plastic ring of the jogwheel will temporarily change the tempo like when "
"vinyl mode is off. Touching the metal disc simulates touching the vinyl "
"record, so just putting your hand on it will stop the “vinyl”. You can "
"scratch in a similar way as with turntables in vinyl mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:108
msgid "Slip mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:110
msgid ""
"By pressing shift + “vinyl / slip” you can toggle slip mode. When entering "
"slip mode, Mixxx remembers what point exactly of the track should be playing"
" even if, for example, you scratch or make a loop. When you press shift + "
"slip again, Mixxx will jump back to that point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:114
msgid "Pads - lower row"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:116
msgid ""
"The play and cue pads should be self-explaining. The sync pad toggles sync "
"lock for a deck, which tries to beatmatch the deck with the others, and also"
" syncs the tempo between them, even when the tempo of one deck is changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:118
msgid "Additional functions can be accessed by holding shift"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:123
msgid "Shift + play"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:123
msgid "Plays the track in reverse and enables slipping (see slip mode)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:124
msgid "Shift + cue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:124
msgid ""
"Brakes the track as if the power of the motor on a turntable was turned off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:125
msgid "Shift + sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:125
msgid ""
"Enables quantize mode (this makes most actions, e.g. pressing play or "
"setting the cue point, fall to the nearest beat)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:129
msgid "Pads - hot cue mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:131
msgid ""
"In hot cue mode the upper row of pads control the hotcues. Pressing a pad "
"that is not lit sets a hotcue. Pressing a pad that is lit makes the track "
"jump and play from that hotcue. Pressing a pad while holding shift deletes "
"that hotcue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:134
msgid ""
"You can control a set of 4 more hotcues by pressing shift + hot cue. The hot"
" cue button will start blinking. The pads will behave in the same way, but "
"controlling hotcues 5 to 8."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:137
msgid "Pads - auto loop mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:139
msgid ""
"Pressing the pads in auto loop mode will make loops of a specific length "
