#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:213
msgid "Effects"
msgstr "Efectos"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:215
msgid ""
"The knob controls the dry/wet knob of the whole effect chain when no effect "
"is focused. When an effect is focused, the knob controls the metaknob of the"
" focused effect. Focus an effect by pressing one of the effect buttons. To "
"switch the controller’s knob back to manipulating the dry/wet knob, unfocus "
"by pressing the button of the focused effect again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:218
msgid ""
"Press and hold an effect button to toggle the enable switch for that effect."
" The enable switches for each effect are not shown on the controller’s LEDs,"
" so you need to look at the screen to check whether an effect is on. All "
"effects are off when Mixxx starts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:221
msgid ""
"Use shift and the mixer knobs to control the parameters of the focused "
"effect. The trim knob controls parameter 1, the equalizer knobs control "
"parameters 2-4, and the filter knob controls parameter 5."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:223
msgid ""
"The DDJ-SB2 does not have enough buttons to control assigning effect units "
"to different decks. You may want to set up a :ref:`custom keyboard mapping "
"<advanced-keyboard>` to have easy access to those switches. Otherwise, you "
"can use your mouse to click the buttons on screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:228
msgid "Auto DJ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:230
msgid ""
"Start/stop Auto DJ: Shift + DECK 4. If enabled in the user options enabled, "
"the level meter LEDs twinkle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:232
msgid "Skip Track: Shift + DECK 3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:235
msgid "Channel fader start"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb2.rst:237
msgid ""
"By moving a channel fader up from the very bottom while holding shift when a"
" deck is paused, the deck will start playing. Moving the fader back to the "
"bottom without releasing shift stops the deck and moves it back to its "
"original position."
msgstr ""
